      "subjects_id": [
        1
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ans. B) Due to defect in NADH Coenzyme Q oxidase</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option B:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Mitochondrial DNA </strong>is inherited cytoplasmically and therefore <strong>transmitted maternally.</strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Mutations </strong>in <strong>mitochondrial DNA </strong>causes:</span></span></span>\r\n\t<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n\t\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Lethal infantile mitochondrial ophthalmoplegia</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Leber&rsquo;s hereditary optic neuropathy </strong>(LHON)</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Myoclonic epilepsy</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Mitochondrial encephalomyopathy lactic acidosis stroke like episodes (MELAS)</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t</ul>\r\n\t</li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">There are <strong>hundreds of copies </strong>of <strong>mitochondrial genes </strong>per cell <strong>(heteroplasmy).</strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Streptomycin </strong>induced <strong>deafness </strong>is also found to be due to a <strong>mutation </strong>in the <strong>mitochondrial rRNA.</strong></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Explanation:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option A. Due to mutations in mitochondrial DNA:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> <strong>LHON </strong>is caused by <strong>point mutations </strong>in <strong>mitochondrial DNA </strong>that lead to <strong>impaired mitochondrial function</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option C. Maternally transmitted:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> Since <strong>LHON </strong>is a <strong>mitochondrial disorder</strong>, it follows a <strong>maternal inheritance pattern </strong>because <strong>mitochondria</strong> are <strong>inherited from the mother</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option D. Affects younger age group:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong> LHON </strong>typically presents in <strong>young adults</strong>, making this statement <strong>true</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Leber&rsquo;s hereditary optic myopathy&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">is characterized by<strong> blindness in young males </strong>and caused by a <strong>single base mutation </strong>in <strong>NADH Coenzyme Q reductase</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ref</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: DM Vasudevan 9/e: p 621, 650</span></strong></span></span></p>",
